Text.Value: My door is always open. Stone Lord.

EditorData.NodeContext: Agreeing to the truce for now, but should contain a hint of threat. Calling him Stone Lord is a reminder that they're not friends.

Text.Value: Aye, I remember the spot - by a garden on the Wide. A soft thicket near the market, with ample pockets to pick. Celestia itself, to a street rat looking for shelter.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wry and rueful, remembering it with fond amusement - Nine-Fingers was abducted as a child and, even after being ransomed, left her family to fend for herself. She doesn't speak of her traumatic past with any great pathos - she's seen worse in the city.

Text.Value: Like a berserker lodge of my homeland. No army or militia, serving the local lords - but heroes, working for the common good!

EditorData.NodeContext: Dawning, gaining enthusiasm at the idea

Text.Value: You are right - I have proven myself unworthy. I cannot serve the city if I was so easily turned against it. If I do not know my own mind... perhaps I no longer know what is good.

EditorData.NodeContext: Enthusiasm dissipating to dejection again. Genuine, quiet doubt - not melodramatic

Text.Value: Good. I'd rather you die as Minsc the mad Rashemaar. It's silly, but - d'you know you were something of a hero of mine, when I was young?

EditorData.NodeContext: To Minsc. Not sentimental, just stating a curious fact before we get to the killing. Amusement at herself on the second line.

Text.Value: You tried, Harper. Don't worry - I never expected you'd let your friend die without a fight. That's one of the reasons I liked you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging, pragmatic - she genuinely likes and respects Jaheira, but knows that if Minsc dies, so must she. Won't hold it against Jaheira for trying to kill her in return, it's inevitable.

Text.Value: ...bah! You try to dampen Boo's eyes. Do not think you will be spared his teeth! Evil is evil, even if it once was... innocent.

EditorData.NodeContext: Emotional at the story and pouring it all into his denial instead. His loudness is proportional to his depth of feeling.

Text.Value: You have nothing to prove to her. You don't belong in the Guild.
You might have knocked it out. But a good thing you did - he's more like his old self again.

EditorData.NodeContext: In response to player saying they knocked sense into Minsc - but satisfied

Text.Value: Minsc, calm down. The battle is over.
She's right, Minsc. She's been an ally down through the years. A friend, even.
Boo?

EditorData.NodeContext: Surprised

Text.Value: ... what?

EditorData.NodeContext: Bemusement cutting through her bloodlust for a moment

Text.Value: Can't we just go back to killing one another instead?
Minsc - Astele -

EditorData.NodeContext: At a loss - wanting to keep the peace between them but knowing it's going to come to blows.

Text.Value: With you? Minsc has no lust for gold, that he would shake grandmothers by their ankles, or set Boo nibbling at their purse-strings!

EditorData.NodeContext: Indignant at the idea of joining the Guild

Text.Value: Even now, your tongue twists the truth. When you were young and ten-fingered still, Minsc and Boo were stone - enstatuated on a city square!

EditorData.NodeContext: Scornful, thinking Nine-Fingers is just trying to lie to him in order to be spared

Text.Value: No. Minsc has not always done what is right - but evil is evil. It is a choice - and Nine-Fingers made hers a long time ago.
If you can't tell ally from enemy, Minsc, maybe you're no hero at all.
And, Tyr's honest truth... you gave my Guild the wake-up call it needed. We've grown complacent, lazy. Too sure of our standing.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging, coming clean

Text.Value: What say you, Boo? When the Absolute is slain, shall we join Nine-Fingers Keene and show her the ways of goodness?
Oh, I'm no innocent. But evil? You tell me. With the Fist, the watch,  and the Council itself all licking the Absolute's boots, who's the only one left standing to protect Baldur's Gate?

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging, not buying Minsc's black and white. She's fervent proud about the Guild's place as the city's true defender, and won't be told otherwise

Text.Value: That story you told... if it be true, then... I am sorry I could not save you then.
She's right. The Guild will fight for the city - we just have to let them.
You have planted a burr in my brain, guildmaster. Once I have dislodged the worm and redeemed myself in my hamster's eyes... we will return to this matter.

EditorData.NodeContext: Nodding, assuming a more grave tone - the matter is shelved for now, and he and 9F might well go back to fighting when all of this is done.

Text.Value: You might not have been wrestling monsters, but... you kept the wind and the rain off. Heroic enough for me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrug - again denying any sentimentality, just stating facts.

Text.Value: So the hound answers to his name again, does he? And you didn't have to put him down.

EditorData.NodeContext: to player, finally clicking that Minsc is back to himself

Text.Value: With the Stone Lord off my back, I'll be able bring my people out of hiding. Cobble together a force so we're ready when you call on us.
Very well - Minsc and Boo accept!
Heh. Jaheira says she is no wychlaran. Perhaps not. But if she says I should not honour, defend, and listen to her... it is the only time she has ever been wrong.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Heh' is not a laugh so much as a quiet grunt of acknowledgement. He's coming around, and knows he has to listen

Text.Value: He's threatening you. Feel threatened.
You have been a stone in this city's boot for too long. And it will be no Stone Lord who reaches 'twixt Balduran's sticky toes to dislodge you - it will be Minsc!

EditorData.NodeContext: Powering through, oblivious of Nine-Fingers' confusion

Text.Value: We need to focus on the Absolute. You can negotiate your alliance afterwards.
...All right. Fine. Let's leave this particular fight for when the actual war is won, shall we?
Kind of you to take the Zhentarim down first, but that doesn't make us friends.
He's been like this ever since I knocked some sense back into him.
I'm sorry, you... you what?
The some sorry tale as yours, then? Bizarre as it is - it explains how this idiot wound up serving the Dead Three.

EditorData.NodeContext: Knows she should doubt our story, but doesn't

Text.Value: We never would've needed the Zhent if we'd had a fighting force of our own. Swords for the city, when the watch and Fist fail us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Convincing Minsc he could be a force for good - it should be an open question whether she's sincere or not, not obviously cunning or overly earnest. 'Sure, why not?'

Text.Value: I can't speak for your rodent, but I know something of debts. If you reckon you've got one to repay... well, we could always work together.

EditorData.NodeContext: Broaching the topic - attempting an olive branch

Text.Value: Simple, then. Trust that Boo will guide you both.
Boo?

EditorData.NodeContext: Surprised and alarmed

Text.Value: Come on then, Stone Lord - if you mean to take my chair, you'll get no better chance than this.

EditorData.NodeContext: Just after one battle but her blood is up now and she's ready for us to attack - urging us to do it

Text.Value: You have my thanks. Though I'm still not actually sure you haven't made my life that little bit harder.
A friend? Jaheira, Boo cannot believe his ears! Has the city fallen so far in our absence? Are there no heroes left?
You did say he was your hero, Astele. Maybe you'll learn something.

EditorData.NodeContext: Amused, enjoying how even Nine-Fingers can't rein Minsc in when he gets going

Text.Value: Explain it all - the tadpole, the Absolute, his time as the Stone Lord.
Proof that he is back to normal, no?
The Zhent are down - just you and me now, Stone Lord. So if you mean to take my chair, you'll get no better chance than this.

EditorData.NodeContext: Just after one battle but her blood is up now and she's ready for us to attack - urging us to do it
EditorData.logicalname: COM - ALT. GREETING IF TRIGGERED PRE-BATTLE COM

Text.Value: Heroes come and go, but the Guild has always been here, protecting the city. Until the Stone Lord came to break us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Still ready to fight and kill Minsc - not letting him off the hook for what he's done

Text.Value: Minsc has no interest in your furniture, Nine-Fingers - only in the wicked rump that fills it!

EditorData.NodeContext: Stressing that he's Minsc and not the Stone Lord

Text.Value: Oh, you fool. I didn't need saving - from you, or anyone else. But - I suppose I'm sorry, too.
I'm not talking about that. We've both got bigger enemies than one another - the city's enemies.

EditorData.NodeContext: Amused by Minsc's misapprehension

Text.Value: Yes. I may not be able to trust my mind, but I trust my friend. Evil is evil - it is a choice and you made yours a long time ago.
Heroes. Sure.

EditorData.NodeContext: Not quite how she'd have phrased it

Text.Value: History will remember the Stone Lord as far worse a villain than Nine-Fingers. Don't make it worse.
That's... not even slightly what I was saying. I wasn't asking -
My friend, I am touched by your kind words. And now I must be equal to them!

EditorData.NodeContext: Not getting that we may have just insulted him

Text.Value: If she trusts in Nine-Fingers - if you do - then so will Minsc. But that means, the things Minsc has done...
...I am shamed. Nydeshka, unworthy to fight alongside my friends! Boo - what am I to do?

EditorData.NodeContext:
Quietly devastated (or quietly for Minsc)
He's seeing how much damage he did as the Stone Lord, and declaring himself ny-DESH-kah - 'Blunt Blade' in Rashemi custom, a berserker who cannot be trusted to fight alongside his friends, and so is given a blunt blade in order to do no harm.

Text.Value: I haven't got the slightest idea what he's trying to say.

EditorData.NodeContext: shrugging at the player, start contrast to Minsc' grand pronouncements

Text.Value: Enough, Nine-Fingers. Minsc has been manipulated enough.
Minsc, I'm fairly certain that 'good' is literally the only thing you do know.
I'm confused, if that counts. But if he no longer answers to Stone Lord...

EditorData.NodeContext: to player

Text.Value: Boo and I will be your berserker lodge, taking the ugly ways of your Guild and beating them into a more virtuous shape!
Boo. Kingpin Boo! My friend - your wisdom is vast and unknowable as the Rashemi High Country!

EditorData.NodeContext: 'OF COURSE!'

Text.Value: A bizarre tale - but it fits this idiot, somehow. But if he's back to himself...
Well, ranger? You cannot always leave it up to your wychlaran. Make a choice.

Synopsis:
Note: OOM is moved to separate dialog

Minsc confronts Nine-Fingers after their temporary truce until the Zhent were defeated. He means to kill her, but she tries to convince him that the Guild is ultimately a force for good within the city.
